On Sat, 28 Aug 1999, Matthew wrote:
> I've read tuning tips wrt Oracle on Linux.  Most say to increase
> SHMMAX and the semaphores.  I ask you this, what _real_ difference
> does it make?  Am I going to be able to see the difference on a VA3500
> (quad pent III 550,512M RAM)?  I'd much rather use a stock kernel, but
> I'll hack for the good of my users.
I presume you'd be running a 2.2 kernel, in which case SHMMAX is
tunable via /proc/sys/kernel/shmmax.
You appear to be limited to 128 semaphore ids at 32 sems per id.
I've never really used SysV IPC, but I suspect that 4K semaphores
"should be enough for anybody".
Matthew.
